had to be good enough to drop those warders once we were in there.<br><br>Do these last two points out weight or counter balance the previous five? Not on your life. <p>Kzan Verto<BR>Giver of "da juice" (tm)<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=220314" target="new">My Magelo Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubippinfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bippinfv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elf-hugger</span><br>  Posts: 699<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/14/02 3:30:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1199.topic&index=15>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Does Firiona Vie live up to your expectations?</span><hr size=1> Not having been to the end-game, ever, I can only speculate, but I think from what I read here between the lines, Kzan, that the big free ride item is the sparse population and lack of competition. FaF and Reso basically had the whole end game to themselves now for some time. That gives you the opporunity to farm mobs that you would have to schedule for months in advance on other servers, doesn't it? Add the tradability of items to that, so those nice drops not only don't go to waste, but get passed down when better is found for original owner. Add the neutral leader inviting both goods and evils and even that was not a big issue (though FaF always maintained that lack of pallies was not hindering them, vice versa *giggle*).<br>All that is not to say that you don't need dedication, teamwork, good strategy a