3t game of level after level and so on, for something more fun... namely rp.<br><br>On my native server I ran a guild dedicated to RP and let me tell you it was HARD. The server was chock full of the most uber l33t you could ever hope to meet and thus my (our) efforts, though successful and rewarding, remained always at odds with the majority of the player comunity.<br><br>So, when I returned to EQ I came here to FV and asked many of my old friends if they cared to join me. Some said yes, some said no. And this is what I have found...<br><br>Love the limited No-drop rules.<br>Love the trivial loot rules.<br>Like the languages rules (wish they were still tougher)<br>Like the one character per server (simply for the lack of twinks and a more level playing field for all)<br>Love the lower population counts over all.<br>Love the lack of uber-wannabees.<br><br>I found many people who rp and many more who humor me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Which is much preferable to the ridicule common on &quot;that other&quot; server. Most of all I have found that the people here are simply nicer. Perhaps more mature but certainally more friendly and helpful.<br><br>I have found a few things I do not care for...<br><br>I do not like that grouping restrictions were removed. <br>I do not like that casters bind same as melee. (I am melee)<br>I wish languages were more difficult to train.<br>I wish (only slightly) that certain open area zones were declared pvp for racial/alignment conflicts. (avoid the zone if ya wish or come and enjoy the fun)<br>I think the economy is highly inflated for no apparent reason.<br><br>Mostly though, FV has been a great deal of fun and has reinvigorated my desire to play. I think it is indeed the best server available to date.<br><br>I'll never go back to another.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td 